This paper deals with the topic of differential privacy, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the generalization properties of adaptive data analyses, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the study of max-information, which is a measure of the sensitivity of a function to changes in the input data, and is relevant to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the composition of algorithms, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Overall, the paper covers a broad range of topics, but the focus on differential privacy and machine learning suggests that cs.CR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories.
